[07:57.67]	'Let us make head.' It was your presurmise,
[08:00.33]	That, in the dole of blows, your son might drop:
[08:03.34]	You knew he walk'd o'er perils, on an edge,
[08:06.12]	More likely to fall in than to get o'er;
[08:08.78]	You were advised his flesh was capable
[08:11.38]	Of wounds and scars and that his forward spirit
[08:14.51]	Would lift him where most trade of danger ranged:
[08:17.69]	Yet did you say 'Go forth;' and none of this,
[08:20.47]	Though strongly apprehended, could restrain
[08:23.30]	The stiff-borne action: what hath then befallen,
[08:26.37]	Or what hath this bold enterprise brought forth,
[08:29.49]	More than that being which was like to be?
[08:32.27]LORD BARDOLPH	We all that are engaged to this loss
[08:34.76]	Knew that we ventured on such dangerous seas
[08:37.71]	That if we wrought our life 'twas ten to one;
[08:40.60]	And yet we ventured, for the gain proposed
[08:43.38]	Choked the respect of likely peril fear'd;
[08:46.15]	And since we are o'erset, venture again.
[08:48.76]	Come, we will all put forth, body and goods.
[08:51.53]MORTON	'Tis more than time: and, my most noble lord,
[08:54.31]	I hear for certain, and do speak the truth,
[08:57.09]	The gentle Archbishop of York is up
[08:59.52]	With well-appointed powers: he is a man
[09:02.12]	Who with a double surety binds his followers.
[09:05.07]	My lord your son had only but the corpse,
[09:07.79]	But shadows and the shows of men, to fight;
[09:10.57]	For that same word, rebellion, did divide
[09:13.23]	The action of their bodies from their souls;
[09:16.12]	And they did fight with queasiness, constrain'd,
[09:19.19]	As men drink potions, that their weapons only
[09:22.14]	Seem'd on our side; but, for their spirits and souls,
[09:25.44]	This word, rebellion, it had froze them up,
[09:28.16]	As fish are in a pond. But now the bishop
[09:30.88]	Turns insurrection to religion:
[09:33.02]	Supposed sincere and holy in his thoughts,
[09:35.79]	He's followed both with body and with mind;
[09:38.63]	And doth enlarge his rising with the blood
[09:41.46]	Of fair King Richard, scraped from Pomfret stones;
[09:44.65]	Derives from heaven his quarrel and his cause;
